==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bilander
<hw>Bil"an*der</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>bijlander</ets>; <ets>bij</ets> by + <ets>land</ets> land,
country.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A small two-masted merchant
vessel, fitted only for coasting, or for use in canals, as in
Holland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Why choose we, then, like <qex>bilanders</qex> to creep⟦br⟧
Along the coast, and land in view to keep?</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bilateral</ent>⟦br⟧
